						<summary>

						<p>North wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Siddhanāthasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vikramachōḷa Year 5: 1122-23 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription in the absence of the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> of the king may be assigned on palaeographical grounds to c. 12th century.</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of one <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> deposited into the temple treasury by Nakkaṉ Aṇḍa[m*]mai, wife of Amudaṅkōvan, a merchant of Avaṉinārāyaṇapuram for maintaining a <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamp to the deity from out of the interest <hi rend="italic">(virutti)</hi> on the above amount.</p>						

						<p>The name of the deity is probably Siddhīśvaram-uḍaiyār.</p>						

						</summary>
